p: Our digestibility results show that N. oculata co-product contained higher amounts of protein compared to N. oculata whole cells (50% vs. 38%) but had significantly lower digestibility values for crude protein than the whole cells (74% vs. 81%). Our reported ADC of crude protein in the N. oculata whole cells ingredient is comparable to levels reported for microalgal whole cells in tilapia, including Chlorella sp. (80%) and Schzochytrium sp. (82%) [ 33], and Anabaena sp.[ 49]. The ADC of crude protein in the N. oculata whole cells and N. oculata co-product ingredients was lower than some other commonly used proteins sources, Spirulina, fishmeal, and soybean meal. And it was higher than the ADC of crude protein in some crops used as protein and carbohydrates sources, including corn, broken rice, sorghum, wheat middlings and rice bran, which have ranged from 57% (sorghum) to 73% (corn) in tilapia [ 33, 50].
